  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240°C/ 220°C (fan)/ gas 9, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on)<strong> </strong>into thin fries, then toss them in a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-30 min or until they're cooked through and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
